    <p class="intro">Ultimately we are a publically held enterprise and so good corporate governance is a responsibility to our investors and critical to the long-term viability of our company. We comply or exceed governance codes used in the United States. We use a one-tier management system, with ten people on our board of directors, eight of whom are independent. Our board committees include: Audit; Compensation; Governance and Nominating; Finance; and Anti-Trust Compliance.</p>
    
